# encrypt the canonical "Ladies and Gentlemen" plaintext under the
# RFC's key/nonce/aad and confirm ciphertext||tag matches the
# published bytes. Locks in correctness against the published vector.
D31A8D34648E60DB7B86AFBC53EF7EC2A4ADED51296E08FEA9E2B5A736EE62D63DBEA45E8CA9671282FAFB69DA92728B1A71DE0A9E060B2905D6A5B67ECD3B3692DDBD7F2D778B8C9803AEE328091B58FAB324E4FAD675945585808B4831D7BC3FF4DEF08E4B7A9DE576D26586CEC64B61161AE10B594F09E26A7E902ECBD0600691
# RFC 7539 decrypt round-trip yields plaintext.
Ladies and Gentlemen of the class of '99: If I could offer you only one tip for the future, sunscreen would be it.
# AES-GCM-256 NIST CAVS gcmEncryptExtIV256.rsp count-0:
